The surrender charge is a percentage of the accumulation value surrendered that is associated with the premium and declines over time.
A Market Value Adjustment (MVA) may increase or decrease the amount of your surrender if more than the charge free amount is surrendered before the end of the 7th contract year.
Charges may differ for some states.

 

Additional Details




Guarantees are based on the claims-paying ability of Voya Insurance and Annuity Company (VIAC)
This is a summary only. Read the contract for complete details. The product and its features may not be available in all states and are subject to change. Withdrawals may be subject to Federal/State income tax and, if taken prior to age 59½, an additional 10% Federal penalty tax.
Contract Form Series: ICC16 VI-IA-3165, VI-IA-3165(2016) (Rev 12/16); Rider Form Series: ICC16 VI-RA-3166, VI-RA-3166(2016) (Rev 12/16), ICC16 VI-RA-3167, VI-RA-3167(2016) (Rev 12/16), VI-RA-3168(2016), may vary by state, and may not be available in all states.
Contract is issued by Voya Insurance and Annuity Company (VIAC), Des Moines, IA.







