forms

 Product Fact Sheet








Benefits



Easy Access+

Payments Can Be Sent to a Third Party
Payments can be automatically sent to single or multiple third parties, and used to pay certain expenses. Payments are still considered taxable.

Direct Deposit
Payments can be sent as a direct deposit to your client’s checking or savings accounts.


Protection Options+

Protection for Your Survivors
With the exception of the Life Payment Plan payout option, which ceases payments upon death, all other payout options allow for a beneficiary to receive any remaining benefits due.

Guaranteed Income
Unless the Increasing Payment Plan or Joint Life option is selected, the amount and frequency of the payments will never change.


Payout Options+


Voya SPIA offers a wide variety of payout options as well as a choice of monthly, quarterly, semiannual or annual payment schedules.
Life Payment Plan with Joint Survivor with Period Certain
Payments until the first death with minimum payment period guaranteed (5-20 years). Following the guaranteed payment period, the payment amount could change based on which annuitant dies first.

Life Payment Plan with Period Certain
Payments for a lifetime with a minimum payment period (5-20 years).

Life Payment Plan with Joint Survivor
Payments until the first death, then amount paid could change based on which annuitant dies first.

Life Payment Plan with Cash Refund
Payments for a lifetime; at death, the purchase payment less applicable premium taxes received will be paid to the beneficiary as a lump sum payment.

Life Payment Plan with Installment Refund
Payments until the later date of death, or until the sum of payments equal the purchase payment, less applicable premium taxes.

Life Payment Plan
Payments for a lifetime, ceasing at death. Payments received may not equal initial premium.

Joint and Last Survivor
Guaranteed regular payments for the owner’s lifetime and the lifetime of another person, such as their spouse. Payments may reduce upon first death.

Joint and Last Survivor with Period Certain
Payments for the owner’s lifetime and the lifetime of another person with a minimum payment period (5-20 years). Once the payout option is chosen, payments are guaranteed for the amount and duration described in the annuity contract.

Increasing Payment Plan Option
To help adjust for inflation, the Increasing Payment Plan option can be added to Voya SPIA. Your client can select annual payment increases of 3% on life contingent contracts or 6% on period certain contracts. For Joint Life payment plan options with increasing income, 100% to survivor must be chosen. The increasing rate is compounded annually regardless of frequency selected.






Eligibility and Premiums



Issue Ages+

35-80 Period  Certain contracts can be purchased between the ages of 0 and 100.


Premium+

Single premium immediate
Minimum premium of $15,000
Maximum premium of $2,000,000 without prior home office approval


Tax Advantages+

Retirement Plan Distributions
Payments are fully taxable and will also be subject to an additional 10% federal penalty tax if received before age 59½, unless an exception applies. However, since these payments are made over time, tax liability is spread out over time as well. Deferring payments can place your clients in lower tax bracket at the time of these payouts, for lower income tax rates.

Partially-Taxable Payments
Only the interest portion of an annuity payment from a non-qualified annuity is taxable. The difference between the total annuity payment and the excludable amount is subject to federal income tax and, if applicable, state income tax. This partial exclusion from income tax continues until the principal is recovered, at which point the annuity payments are fully taxable.


Additional Details+

Annuities are issued by Voya Insurance and Annuity Company, a member of the Voya® family of companies.
Contract Form Series: 1823
All guarantees are based upon the financial strength and claims-paying ability of Voya Insurance and Annuity Company, which is solely responsible for all obligations under its contracts.
This is a summary only. Read the contract for complete details.
The product and its features may not be available in all states and are subject to change. Withdrawals may be subject to Federal/State income tax and, if taken prior to age 591 ⁄2, an additional 10% Federal penalty tax.
All distributions from qualified annuities may be taxable. State premium taxes may reduce the final value of your annuity.
IRAs and other qualified plans already provide tax-deferral like that provided by an annuity. Additional features and benefits such as contract guarantees, death benefits and the ability to receive a lifetime income are contained within the annuity for a cost. Please be sure the features and costs of the annuity are right for your clients when considering the purchase of the annuity.
Neither the company nor its agents or representatives can provide tax, legal or accounting advice. Please consult your attorney or tax advisor about your specific circumstances. Immediate annuities have no cash value, cannot be surrendered, and provide only the benefit described in the contract.
